Electricity bill Generator :

First 50==free
next 50==3
next 50==5
next 50==8
next 50==10
next 50==20

//
import java.util.Scanner;

class elec
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
   Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
   System.out.println("Electricity bill generator");
   System.out.print("Enter the Due Amount:");
   int due=sc.nextInt();
   System.out.print("Enter the Units Consumed:");    
   double unit=sc.nextInt();
   double amt=0;
   if(unit<=50)
     amt=amt+due;
   else if(unit>50 && unit <=100)
     amt=(unit-50)*3 +due;
   else if(unit>100 && unit<=150)
     amt=(50 * 3) + ((unit-100)*5 )+ due;
   else if(unit>150 && unit <=200)
    amt=(50 * 3) + (50 * 5) + ((unit - 150)*8) + due;
   else if(unit>200 && unit <=250)
    amt=(50 * 3) + (50 * 5) + (50 * 8) + ((unit - 200)*10) + due;
   else 
    amt=(50 * 3) + (50 * 5) + (50 * 8) * ( 50 * 10)* ((unit-250)* 20);
   double disc=0;
   System.out.println("Bill amount without Discount="+amt);
   disc=amt*0.20;
   amt=amt-disc;
   System.out.println("Bill amount after Discount="+amt);
   System.out.print("Discount="+disc);

   }
}
//

Switch statement :

Syntax:
 
switch(value/expression/variable)
{
	case value/expression:
	break;
	case value expression:
	break;
	
	default:
}

=> In Switch  statements double , float , long , boolean are not allowed.


Looping Statements:

While Loop:
Sum of all the integers using while loop.
Finding the Factorial using While lopp.
Printing all the even numbers.

Examplar program on Printing sum of all the Digits given :

//
class SumDigit 
{
public static void main(String[]args)
{
int num=123;
int sum=0;
int rem=0;

while(num>0)
{
rem=num%10;
sum+=rem;
num=num/10;
}
system.out.println("Sum of all the digits is :"+sum);
}
}
//



Examplar program on PALINDROME:

//
import java.util.Scanner;

class a{
public static void main(String []args)
{
Scanner scan= new Scanner(System.in);
int i=0,n=0,s=0;
System.out.println("Enter the  numbers:");
i=scan.nextInt();
int temp =i;
while(i!=0)
{

n=i%10;
s=s*10+n;
n=n/10;
}
System.out.println(s);
if(temp==s)
{
System.out.println("it is a Palindrome ");
else 
System.out.println("It is not a palindrome");
}
}
}
